I"*<p>Ivan is from Villavicencio, Colombia. He studied Physics and then obtained a Masters degree on Biomedical Sciences both at Universidad de Los Andes in Bogota. Ivan joined the Biophysics PhD program at University of Maryland in the fall of 2013 and joined our lab a year after. His main research interest is how the self-assembly and dynamic structure of cytoskeletal filaments allow cells to change shape and regulate many processes. In his free time, Ivan enjoys exploring the forests and jungles in search of animals to capture with his camera.</p>
